course: main course
cuisine: North America
---

In a small #pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups} (2 1/4 cups for 4 servings), @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to use in Step 4.

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice @Yellow Onion{1} into ¼-inch pieces. Dice @Celery{2.5%ounce} into ¼-inch pieces. Halve, core, and dice @Bell Pepper{1} into ¼-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add onion and cook, stirring, until translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove sausage from casing if necessary; discard casing. Add @Italian Pork Sausage Mix{9%ounce} to pan along with celery, bell pepper, scallion whites, @Cajun Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, and @Hot Smoked Paprika{1%teaspoon}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Increase heat under pan with sausage mixture to high. Add another drizzle of oil and cooked rice; stir until well combined and warmed through. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Remove from heat.

Divide dirty rice between #bowls{}. Drizzle with @Smoky Red Pepper Crema{4%tablespoon} and sprinkle with scallion greens. Serve.

> Pork Sausage is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.